                <p><span class="style1"><strong> HUERTA MEDIATION</strong> provides mediation and arbitration services for businesses, and for individuals by lawyer referral. For the past twenty years,  HUERTA MEDIATION has been helping lawyers and clients find reasonable, confidential, interest-based and expeditious resolutions to their commercial, <a href="PracticeAreas.shtml">employment,</a> including discrimination, <u><a href="PracticeAreas.shtml">sexual harassment</a></u>, <u><a href="PracticeAreas.shtml">private attorney general act (PAGA)</a></u>, <u><a href="PracticeAreas.shtml">wage and hour,</a></u> and <u><a href="PracticeAreas.shtml">wrongful termination</a></u>, <u><a href="PracticeAreas.shtml">real estate</a></u>, insurance, intellectual property, <u><a href="PracticeAreas.shtml">securities</a></u>, tort, and personal injury cases through mediation, arbitration and facilitation resolution services.</span>
                </p>

                <p>&nbsp;</p>

                <p><strong>WHY CHOOSE  HUERTA MEDIATION?</strong></p>

                <p><a href="http://www.huertamediation.com/DynamicAttorneys.shtml" target="_self">
                    <strong>Principal Mediator Lawrence A. Huerta</strong></a> <span class="style1">has mediated more than 1000 business, employment, real estate, insurance coverage, securities, trades secrets, defamation and tort cases.  Mr. Huerta has mediated more than 500 employment cases, including discrimination, sexual harassment, a nation-wide sexual discrimination and harassment class action, PAGA, wage and hour, and wrongful termination cases. Mr. Huerta serves on the Amercian Arbitration Association (AAA), the Financial Industry Regulatory Authority (FINRA), the San Diego County Superior Court and the California Department of Insurance Mediation Panels. Mr. Huerta also arbitrates  commercial employment, real estate, and securities cases for the AAA and FINRA. </span><span
                        style="color: #000000">Mr. Huerta is known for his creative, energetic, and positive approach and his persistence and tenacity in helping parties find interest based, risk managed resolutions.</span>
                </p>

                <p><a href="http://www.huertamediation.com/DynamicAttorneys.shtml"><strong>Attorney, Mediator and
                    Arbitrator Lawrence A. Huerta</strong></a> was selected as one of three mediators in the nation to
                    be in the Inaugural Class of Access ADR Mediation Fellows. He has received extensive training in
                    mediation and arbitration methods, has mediated cases across the country, and has been a speaker
                    about mediation at American Bar Association Annual Dispute Resolution Conferences, the San Diego Bar
                    Association, the Orange County Bar Association, the State Bar of California Annual Labor &amp;
                    Employment Conference, and the Hispanic National Bar Association Annual Convention. Mr. Huerta has
                    also authored the publications&nbsp;&quot;What Lawyers &amp; Clients Are Looking For in Commercial
                    Mediation&quot; and &quot;Why Mediation?,&quot; the MCLE&nbsp;course, &quot;Why Mediation Works and
                    What Works Well at Mediation?,&quot; as well as the MCLE course &quot;How To Make Mediation Work
                    For You and Your Client,&quot;and &quot;What Works Well at Mediation.&quot;</p>

                <p><a href="http://www.huertamediation.com/StaticForm.shtml"><strong>Contact a business, employment, and
                    real estate law mediator at  HUERTA MEDIATION</strong></a> to discuss the specifics
                    of your case and your clients&#39; needs.  HUERTA MEDIATION helps clients find
                    interest-based resolutions to legal disputes throughout San Diego, Orange, Los Angeles, and Imperial
                    counties, including the cities of San Diego, Los Angeles, Vista, El Cajon, Chula Vista, Irvine,
                    Oceanside, Carlsbad, Santa Ana, Fullerton, and Riverside.  HUERTA MEDIATION also provides mediation 
                    services throughout California, through video conferencing, and around the nation.</p>

                <p>&nbsp;</p>


